{
  "description": "SQLite-Snowflake hybrid with aggregate FILTER spelled as WHERE inside parens, PIVOT/UNPIVOT as FROM-clause operators, GROUP BY SUBTOTAL for ROLLUP, and comma-joins using semicolons.",
  "divergence_level": "moderate",
  "inspired_by": [
    "sqlite",
    "snowflake"
  ],
  "name": "sqllite_flake_agg",
  "notes": "Hybrid of SQLite's type-flexible semantics (TYPEOF, IFNULL, || concat, case-insensitive LIKE, division-by-zero\u2192NULL, c_style booleans) with Snowflake's aggregate FILTER-as-WHERE-inside-parens pattern and PIVOT/UNPIVOT FROM-clause support. Distinctive axes: (1) aggregate FILTER clause spelled as WHERE inside aggregate function parentheses (e.g., COUNT(x WHERE x > 5)), (2) PIVOT/UNPIVOT as first-class FROM-clause operators, (3) NULLS LAST as default for BOTH ascending and descending ORDER BY (unusual combo\u2014most engines default NULLS LAST only for ASC), (4) semicolon-required statements. Conflicts with snowacle_qualify on null ordering and CTE spelling; conflicts with redgres_lateral on concat style and window defaults; conflicts with mydb2_rollup on row-limiting and modulo; conflicts with bigmaria_pivot on identifier quoting, array indexing, and set-op syntax.",
